[2] Cholera - Angola (Kwanza Sul)
Date: Wed, 17 May 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Angola Press Agency (Luanda) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200605170810.html>

At least 61 people died of cholera, out of 392 cases recorded in Angola's
central Kwanza-Sul province, between 20 Apr and 15 May 2006, a report says.
According to an appraisal by the Department of Public Health and Control of
Endemic Diseases delivered to Angop, Sumbe district recorded 258 cases and
21 deaths, Amboim (78) and 27 deaths, Kilenda (31) and 3 deaths, Conda (18)
and 4 deaths and Libolo (7) and 6 deaths. The source warned of a shortage
of medicines and disposable material to handle the situation.
******
[3] Cholera - Angola (Huila)
Date: Tue, 16 May 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Angola Press Agency (Luanda) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200605170588.html>

One of the 2 people that got cholera in Cacula district, Angola's southern
Huila province, died, a health source announced Tue, 16 May 2006.
Local deputy administrator, Miguel Agostinho, added that the 2 cases were
recorded at Viti-Vivali and Viamba sectors and that 3 tents have been
installed to attend possible patients. In order to avoid the spread of the
disease, the local administration has taken some measures such as treatment
of water for human consumption, forbidding the sale of meat and fish at
open black markets, and cleaning campaigns.
******
[4] Cholera - Sudan (south)
Date: Thu, 18 May 2006
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak Reports [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2006_05_18a/en/>

As of 5 May 2006, the cumulative number of cases in southern Sudan is 13
852, with 516 deaths (CFR 3.73 per cent). The outbreak started in Yei at
the end of Jan 2006, and 6 out of 10 states have confirmed cases. The
current focus of the outbreak is in East Equatoria State. A task force
including key partners (WHO and other UN agencies, NGOs) is assisting the
Ministry of Health of southern Sudan to coordinate the response to the
outbreak.
