[7] Cholera - Zimbabwe (Mashonaland Central)
Date: 16 May 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Herald (Harare) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200605160956.html>

Cholera has killed at least 12 people while 26 others were hospitalized in
Kachuta, Guruve District.
Addressing a Civil Protection Committee meeting in Bindura over the
weekend, the provincial medical director for Mashonaland Central Province
Dr Clemence Tshuma said a cholera outbreak has been reported in Guruve,
with the first case having been identified sometime early in May 2006 when
a sick man was diagnosed for cholera.
According to Dr Tshuma, this man had apparently caught the cholera at a
funeral of yet another victim who had died without medical attention. When
a team of health personnel finally visited the area to investigate, it was
further ascertained that about 8 more deaths had occurred in Apr 2006,
apparently as a result of cholera but no notification had been given to
health officials as to the cause of the death.
Health officials said the cholera outbreak had spread even wider as more
cases from as far as Mushumbi Pools, Guruve Centre and Matsitsi have been
reported. "So the outbreak has spread from the epicentre of Kachuta to as
far as Mushumbi Pools, Guruve Centre and Matsitsi," he added.
--
