[8] Cholera, Diarrhea - India (Kashmir)
Date: Wed, 17 May 2006
From ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Greater Kashmir Online [edited]
<http://www.greaterkashmir.com/full_story.asp?Date=18_5_2006&ItemID=31&cat=21>

Several areas of Varmul district and some places in Rafiabad area have been
severely gripped by cholera, causing panic among the population.
The medical faculty of district hospital Varmul told Greater Kashmir that
from the onset of summer, they have received many cases of cholera,
jaundice and other gastrointestinal diseases from the town and its
adjoining areas. "To date we've received 200 to 250 patients including
children suffering from cholera and jaundice, all waterborne diseases," one
of the hospital faculty members Dr Masood said, adding the patients came
from the town and other areas in vicinity.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
